             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> DESCRIPTION</span>{{Underline|4b0082}}
<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia">
'''Level 220''', also known as "EXTRAVAGANZA!", represents a set of huge cities with bright, extravagant aesthetics and flashy explosive patterns.
{{Blurimage|file=Neo4.png|caption=The first photo taken of Level 220.}}

The city's architecture is reminiscent of modern architecture in large tourist metropolises, characterized by non-repetitive, well-organized, and proportional patterns. The entire land is covered in neon lights, both externally, like on buildings and streets, and within structures. These lights remain lit indefinitely, illuminating and decorating the entire region. 

Even with such aesthetics that resemble futurism, the cities do not appear futuristic, but rather have the equivalent technology that is present today in well-developed cities in the frontrooms.

Those cities are likely suitable for large numbers of people, boasting numerous commercial establishments, food services such as restaurants, markets, and shops, as well as leisure facilities such as theaters, casinos, beaches, parks, and more. However, level 220 is devoid of population or individuals.

Cities in the level expand indefinitely and possibly randomly, but have endpoints, where they are connected to other cities by highways and bridges that usually cross seas or small plains. These roads don't appear to extend very far, and it's always possible to see other cities to which they connect from their starting point. Likewise, transportation from one city to another without a vehicle is likely impossible or hard-boiled.

The level is stuck in a nighttime state, thus preserving its aesthetic. The sky is always clear, mostly devoid of clouds, stars, or any other celestial objects. The weather remains consistently moderate and unchanged. Climatic phenomena like wind or rain are also absent in '''Level 220.'''

Since they are always empty, the cities are always clean and properly organized, and, inexplicably, all establishments always operate in perfect condition, restocking their products each time one is used/purchased. Level 220, even possessing characteristics suitable for establishing a large civilization, cannot have more than one individual inside the level at a time. Thus, access to the level is only available when there are no individuals within it. However, it doesn't appear to be a problem due to a phenomenon called the "Extravaganza Function."


</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);color:#FFF0F5; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #4b0082; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px #000000;">

<span style="font-size:30px; font-family:Akaya Telivigala; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em red, 0em 0em 1.0em purple;
background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #800080, #ff69b4, #800080, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%;
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> EXTRAVAGANZA VOUCHER FUNCTION</span>{{Underline|4b0082}}
<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia">
Upon entering '''Level 220''', the individual will wake up inside a subway that arrives at their destination within minutes. Upon exiting the train, to continue through the level, the individual must pass through turnstiles that only open upon receipt of a digital bracelet named "Extravaganza Voucher." With this bracelet, one can visualize a preset time limit that begins to run out from the moment the user places it on their wrist. 

{{Blurimage|file=Neo9.jpg|caption=Another photo taken of Level 220.|width=250x500px}}

The time displayed on the bracelet can vary between 24 and 36 hours. This number represents the amount of time the individual can remain on '''Level 220'''. At the end of the time, the bracelet will guide the user to the nearest subway station, where he will leave the level.

The time shown cannot be increased, but it is likely to be reduced based on the user's activities in the city. It should be noted that any activities performed within '''Level 220''' will result in a loss of available time, such as purchasing products in general. Each product has a set price in stores, as do leisure activities. The user's time will decrease in relation to the price of the product purchased. Typically, most items and activities in cities are expensive; therefore, considering value is recommended. Performing any illegal activity, such as vandalism or theft, will result in significant time loss. 

The user will not be able to leave '''Level 220''' until the time on the bracelet runs out. Failure to exit the level after approximately 1 hour of the bracelet's full time depletion will result in being automatically teleported into the nearest subway station. Upon exiting the level, the bracelet will disappear. 


</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);color:#FFF0F5; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #4b0082; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px #000000;">

<span style="font-size:30px; font-family:Akaya Telivigala; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em red, 0em 0em 1.0em purple;
background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #800080, #ff69b4, #800080, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%;
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> EXTRAVAGANZA WAY</span>{{Underline|4b0082}}
<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia">
The "Extravaganza Way" is the primary subway station on '''Level 220'''. Its architecture resembles large stations seen in the front rooms, but with the addition of the neon aesthetic present on the level.

{{Blurimage|file=Neo8.jpg|caption="Extravaganza Way" from inside.|width=280x280px}}

This station is characterized by its size, comparable to a shopping mall or airport, with establishments such as restaurants and shops, as well as several subway lines that connect to various locations within cities and also to other cities. This is a popular line of stations, with at least one per city. Extravaganza Way subways stand out for their comfort and performance, traveling through cities in minutes.

Like all other products at '''Level 220''', tickets can only be acquired by purchase. However, tickets are not usually expensive.

{{Blurimage|file=Neo10.jpg|caption=Photo taken at the starting point of a blue-styled city in Level 220.|align=left}}


The station has four main lines: the colored line, the pink line, the blue line, and the green line. The colored line is the cheapest and only travels within the city where the station is established. It usually leads to subway exits at important locations, such as large restaurants, shopping malls, and others.

The other lines are responsible for transportation between other cities, each leading to cities themed after their corresponding color. Cities with different colors remain similar overall, with the only notable differences being the color of the lights and slight design changes.

</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);color:#FFF0F5; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #4b0082; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px #000000;">

<span style="font-size:30px; font-family:Akaya Telivigala; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em red, 0em 0em 1.0em purple;
background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ff69b4, #800080, #ff69b4, #800080, #ff69b4);
             background-size: 400%;
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> THE NEON TICKET</span>{{Underline|4b0082}}
<div style="text-align:left;font-family:Georgia">

The Neon Ticket is a rare item that grants access to '''Level 220'''. The ticket resembles a piece of plastic-like material cut into a rectangular shape. It has a unique appearance, featuring a pink color and glowing parts.

On the ticket, there will be a scratch card, which, after being scratched by the holder, will reveal the following phrase: "Enjoy your trip!" Upon scratching, the holder will faint, and then, upon waking, will find himself inside the train that will soon arrive at Extravaganza Way.

Upon arriving at the level station, the ticket holder must insert their ticket at the turnstiles to proceed and then receive their digital bracelet. After this process, it is believed that the ticket is discarded and then made available again. No cases of two tickets coexisting have been reported, so it is assumed that the ticket will only be available when discarded inside '''Level 220'''.

Inexplicably, if the scratch remains unscratched after approximately 5 hours of the encounter, the ticket disappears. That likely occurs because of the possibility that someone may keep the ticket and not use it, preventing anyone else from finding it.

It's speculated that the ticket can be found in any level within the backrooms, usually hidden within whatever the level's scenery offers. Even so, its shiny appearance makes it easy to spot. So far, it hasn't been possible to obtain a photo of the ticket due to its rarity. 



</div>
</div>

<div style="background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);color:#FFF0F5; margin:1em; padding:20px 20px; border:4px solid #4b0082; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px #000000;">

<span style="font-size:30px; font-family:Akaya Telivigala; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em red, 0em 0em 1.0em purple;
